 the material chronologically to give historical perspective and continuity to the whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aCanadian literaturexInuit authors. 0aInuit literaturezCanadavTranslations into English. 0aInuitzCanadavFolklore. 0aInuitzCanadaxHistoryvSources. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Native American.2bisacsh1 aPetrone, Penny, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144267779140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442677791423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442677791/original  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK